tired: Tokenomics 
wired: Tokenology 

I’m excited to share two posts with 1) my thoughts on the next phase of tokens and 2) how to design effective tokens

https://a16zcrypto.com/content/article/beyond-tokenomics-tokenology/

https://a16zcrypto.com/content/article/designing-tokens-sanity-checks-principles-guidance/
Tokenomics (a portmanteau of token and economics) inherently focuses on financial applications of blockchains, but I believe the societal ramifications can be much broader.
Blockchains let us speedrun the creation and destruction of civilizations, allowing *anyone* to design societies at the pace of software instead of the pace of revolution.

I would suggest we rebrand the study of using mechanism design and cryptography to solve coordination problems as “Tokenology.” That’s why I wrote the first piece. https://a16zcrypto.com/content/article/beyond-tokenomics-tokenology/
Designing a good token can be really hard. I believe there isn’t such a thing as a good token model or a bad token model. There is only a token model that achieves your goals as a builder.

I’ve gotten to work on designing tokens, and learned from some of the most prolific builders. I wrote the second piece enumerating the sanity checks I use when designing new tokens https://a16zcrypto.com/content/article/designing-tokens-sanity-checks-principles-guidance/

If you’re passionate about token design, or are working on a project to redesign society, shoot me a DM. If you’re excited about moving beyond financial applications of tokens, please share this thread
